aa(lp16
VThe first piece of the puzzle is remoteness
p17
aVand the quality of education.
p18
aVNow, by remoteness, I mean two or three different kinds of things.
p19
aVOf course, remoteness in its normal sense, which means
p20
aVthat as you go further and further away
p21
aVfrom an urban center, you get to remoter areas.
p22
aVWhat happens to education?
p23
aVThe second, or a different kind of remoteness
p24
aVis that within the large metropolitan areas all over the world,
p25
aVyou have pockets, like slums, or shantytowns, or poorer areas,
p26
aVwhich are socially and economically remote
p27
aVfrom the rest of the city, so it's us and them.
p28
aVWhat happens to education in that context?
