aVAnd finally came the question of, how do you tackle teacher perception?
p97
aVWhenever you go to a teacher and show them some technology,
p98
aVthe teacher's first reaction is,
p99
aVyou cannot replace a teacher with a machine \u2014 it's impossible.
p100
aVI don't know why it's impossible, but, even for a moment,
p101
aVif you did assume that it's impossible \u2014 I have a quotation from Sir Arthur C. Clarke,
p102
aVthe science fiction writer whom I met in Colombo,
p103
aVand he said something which completely solves this problem.
p104
aVHe said a teacher than can be replaced by a machine, should be.
p105
aVSo, you know, it puts the teacher into a tough bind, you have to think.
